-- Venezuela Captures Two Colombian Paramilitary Drug Traffickers
-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 2012-02-07T06:44:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/venezuela-captures-two-colombian-paramilitary-drug-traffickers.html
Venezuela  captured two Colombian
brothers who led a paramilitary group that engaged in drug
trafficking, Interior Minister Tarek El Aissami said.  Venezuelan authorities arrested Hector Buitrago Parada,
alias “Martin Llanos,” and Nelson Orlando Buitrago Parada,
known as “Horse,” on Feb. 4 in eastern Anzoategui state, El
Aissami said in comments carried by state television yesterday.  The Buitrago brothers, wanted for crimes including drug
trafficking and murder, would be delivered immediately to
Colombian authorities, El Aissami said. Colombian President  Juan
Manuel Santos , speaking on the Caracol television network, said
Colombia had 11 warrants out for the arrest of “Martin
Llanos.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
